Cooperation with Czech firm
2016-03-31 01:55:17 GMT
Czech consumer loan company Home Credit's holding company PPF Group signed a strategic cooperation framework agreement late Tuesday in a meeting in Prague with Chinese banking industry representatives.The signing took place during President Xi Jinping's visit to the country."We're confident in the China market to increase the investment up to 6 billion yuan ($926 million) in the coming two years. Our goal is to widen a direct, mutually beneficial collaboration with durable goods' producers across geographies," Home Credit Group CEO Jiri Smejc was quoted as saying in a statement sent to the Global Times on Wednesday.
